	 	<div class="row">
		<h3>What is ComParaLogS?</h3>
	    <p>ComParaLogS is a comparative platform to investigate orthologs and paralogs from tomato and grapevine, defined exploiting a multilevel approach based on similarities detected simultaneously at gene, transcript and protein level (see "About" section). Moreover, reconciled functional descriptions, as well as common or peculiar enzymatic classes and protein domains from tomato and grapevine, together with a trascriptional characterization of both plants, contributed a comprehensive set of information useful to comparatively exploit the two species gene annotations and investigate on differences between species with climacteric and non-climacteric fruits. </p>
		 	<h3>Database search</h3>
            <p>You can search the database typing any keyword (eg.: gene ID, functional definition, other) in the field below. Results will appear while you type a keyword.</p>
		 	<div class="col-lg-9 col-lg-offset-0">
